The National Labor RelationsBoard said it issued an unfair Labor practice complaint againstFirst Union Management, a unit of First Union Real EstateInvestments &lt;FUR>, for discouraging membership in a labororganization.    The NLRB said the complaint asserts First Union Managementhired a cleaning contractor, &lt;Systems Management>, to clean the300 Sixth Avenue Building in Pittsburgh on the condition thatSystems not deal with the Service Employees International Union(SEIU), Local 29.    Jack Yoedt, executive director of SEIU, the janitors union,said that damages could amount to more than 200,000 dlrs inback pay for janitors and that other damages may beforthcoming. Reuter&#3;